    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-09-12T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-09-12T16:00:00-05:00" n="337"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d337">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3231/1015: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-09-12T18:00:00-03:00"
                            >September 12, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 6:47 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>222. My 219, September 9, 6 p.m.<note n="20" xml:id="d337fn20">Not
                        printed.</note> Trade agreement approved by Chamber this afternoon by vote
                    of 127 to 51.</p>
                <p>The agreement will now go to Senate for approval after which it must return to
                    Chamber for signature of the Chairman.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
